'''Aslak Torjusson''' (4 March 1891 – 26 April 1973) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] educator.
He was born in [[Rauland]]. He took teacher's education in [[Holmestrand Seminary|Holmestrand]] in 1912, [[examen artium|finished]] secondary education in 1918 and graduated from the [[University of Oslo|Royal Frederick University]] with the [[cand.philol.]] degree in 1923. While doing so he was a primary school teacher from 1912 to 1920 and then a teacher at [[Telemark Folk High School]] for four years.<ref name=hvem>{{cite encyclopedia|year=1973|title=Torjusson, Aslak|encyclopedia=[[Hvem er hvem?]]|editor=Steenstrup, Bjørn|publisher=Aschehoug|location=Oslo|url=http://runeberg.org/hvemerhvem/1973/0567.html|page=567|language=Norwegian|accessdate=27 July 2013}}</ref><ref name=allkunne>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2013|title=Aslak Torjusson|encyclopedia=[[Allkunne]]|editor=[[Audhild Gregoriusdotter Rotevatn|Rotevatn, Audhild G.]]|publisher=Nynorsk kultursentrum|location=[[Hovdebygda]]|url=http://allkunne.no/default.aspx?menu=370&id=816|language=Norwegian|accessdate=27 July 2013}}</ref>
From 1927 to 1936 he was the secretary of [[Noregs Mållag]]. He was then the headmaster of [[Buskerud Folk High School]] from 1936 to 1952 and lecturer at [[Sagene Teachers' College]] from 1952 to 1961. He was also a board member of the [[Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation]] from 1933 to 1947.<ref name=hvem/>
He issued the book ''Frøydis Haavardsholm og norsk leid i dekorativ kunst'' in 1933.<ref name=hvem/> He did not manage to complete his standard work about Norwegian [[folk high school]]s&mdash;''Den norske folkehøgskulen. Opphav og grunnlag''&mdash;within his lifespan, but it was finished by [[Helge Dahl]] in 1977.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Helge Dahl|encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Knut|last=Jordheim|editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Helge_Dahl/utdypning|language=Norwegian|accessdate=18 September 2009}}</ref>
He died in April 1973.<ref name=allkunne/> His daughter Anne Torjusson Diesen was assisting director of television in the [[Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation]] in the 1990s, and an experienced journalist covering the Norwegian Royal Court. She was married to [[Erik Diesen]].<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Erik Diesen|encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Hans Fredrik|last=Dahl|authorlink=Hans Fredrik Dahl|editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Erik_Diesen/utdypning|language=Norwegian|accessdate=18 September 2009}}</ref><ref>http://www.journalisten.no/story/61499</ref>
