{{orphan|date=April 2015}}
'''Nellai S. Muthu''' (born May 10, 1951) is [[Tamil language|Tamil]] writer and a scientist working at the [[Satish Dhawan Space Centre]]. He has written many technical books and novels based on science in [[Tamil language|Tamil]]. He has won several awards from the Tamil development department of [[Tamil Nadu]] for his works ''Vinveli 2057'', ''Arivutom vingana vilaiyattu'', ''Einsteinum andaveliyum'' and ''Ariviyal varalaru''

==Awards==
Muthu received an award from the government of India's National Council for Science and Technology in 2004 for making science accessible to the public through his books, magazine contributions, and other media.<ref>{{cite web|title=Annual Report 2004-2005|url=http://www.dst.gov.in/about_us/ar04-05s-t.htm|publisher=Department of science and technology|accessdate=6 September 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130914213906/http://www.dst.gov.in/about_us/ar04-05s-t.htm|archivedate=14 September 2013|df=}}</ref> He received the Mahakavi Bharathi Aiynthamizh award in the Ariviyal Tamil category from [[Bharathiar University]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Mahakavi Bharathi Aiynthamizh awards|url=http://www.hindu.com/2008/12/04/stories/2008120451050200.htm|accessdate=6 September 2013|newspaper=The Hindu}}</ref> He also received the Pal Maruthuvar G. Sitrambalanar award for his work ''Evurthiyiyal''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Awards presented to authors of science books in Tamil|url=http://www.hindu.com/2009/10/04/stories/2009100460540600.htm|accessdate=6 September 2013|newspaper=The Hindu}}</ref>

