{{Infobox language |name=Xakriabá |region=[[Minas Gerais]] |states=[[Brazil]] |extinct=1864 |ethnicity=formerly [[Xakriabá people]] |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Macro-Ge languages|Macro-Ge]] |fam2=[[Ge languages|Ge]] |fam3=Central |fam4=Acua |iso3=xkr |glotto=xakr1238 |glottorefname=Xakriaba }}
'''Xakriabá''' (also written '''Chakriaba''', '''Chikriaba''', '''Shacriaba''') is an [[language death|extinct]] [[Jê languages|Ge language]] formerly spoken in [[Minas Gerais]], [[Brazil]] by the [[Xakriabá people]], who today speak [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]].<ref name="moseley-2007"/>
The last confirmed native speaker of the language died in 1864.{{citation needed|date=July 2012}}
